Project description

Python makes loading code dynamically easy, allowing you to configureand extend your application by discovering and loading extensions(”plugins”) at runtime. Many applications implement their ownlibrary for doing this, using __import__ or importlib.stevedore avoids creating yet another extensionmechanism by building on top of setuptools entry points. The codefor managing entry points tends to be repetitive, though, so stevedoreprovides manager classes for implementing common patterns for usingdynamically loaded extensions.
